; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures timer2 and generates a PWM interrupt.
;
; B. Preparation
;    N/A
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. Timer2
;
; C. Default Port
;    1. Timer20 : PC0/PC0 (Output/Capture Input)
;               : PC2 (External Clock Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; Timer20
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (Timer20)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 0 m h 10 1000 ]
;    Source                    : m (MCCR : Misc Clock)
;    MCCR Source               : h (HSI : High Speed Internal Clock - 32MHz)
;    Source Divide             : 10 
;    Timer3 Pre-Divide         : 1000 (MCCR Clock / 10) / 1000
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 0 i o h 3200 6400 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : m (PWM) 
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 3200
;    B Data                    : 6400
;
; Timer20
sendln 'cm timer2'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 m h 10 1000'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i m h 3200 6400'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
